Verifies that if there are multiple concurrent requests to the same URL
beyond the RequestCoalescingCutoff
(assumed to be less than 45 seconds in this test)
that only a single request is sent to the server.

-- cache.txt --
GET http://www.example.com/foo HTTP/1.1
Date: Sat, 01 Jan 2000 00:00:00 GMT

HTTP/1.1 200 OK
Content-Type: text/plain; charset=utf-8
Content-Length: 15
Cache-Control: max-age=604800
Date: Sat, 01 Jan 2000 00:00:50 GMT

Hello, World!
GET http://www.example.com/foo HTTP/1.1
Date: Sat, 01 Jan 2000 00:00:01 GMT

HTTP/1.1 200 OK
Content-Type: text/plain; charset=utf-8
Content-Length: 15
Cache-Control: max-age=604800
Date: Sat, 01 Jan 2000 00:01:00 GMT

Hello, World!
-- server.txt --
GET http://www.example.com/foo HTTP/1.1
Host: www.example.com
Date: Sat, 01 Jan 2000 00:00:00 GMT

HTTP/1.1 200 OK
Content-Type: text/plain; charset=utf-8
Content-Length: 15
Cache-Control: max-age=604800
Date: Sat, 01 Jan 2000 00:00:50 GMT

Hello, World!
GET http://www.example.com/foo HTTP/1.1
Host: www.example.com
Date: Sat, 01 Jan 2000 00:00:01 GMT

HTTP/1.1 200 OK
Content-Type: text/plain; charset=utf-8
Content-Length: 15
Cache-Control: max-age=604800
Date: Sat, 01 Jan 2000 00:01:00 GMT

Hello, World!

